<subSubSection id="D1D9846D27B1D0E835CCC2127B98BC6C" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="note">
<paragraph id="FB258631A8032C862CEE93B9F3C66511" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4AC610E0D39A877ECF60FCC748823D9" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
There is a lot of confusion between 
<taxonomicName id="043B7ACBF5168B43CE1444F13AA3C7E1" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila mirabilis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="25B47D334167374F190F7C395354B498" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66FE9379FF559E9B70D311FCE3DA4C12" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis id="E0E9A5485B8D52384256A7B1D6C748FA" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Butler, 1881) in the literature with regard to illustrations of the adults and genitalia. The taxonomic clarification of this problem will be given in a separate publication.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9ACF5E7DE2B54D0A1F4A4DA2811AF2D0" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="taxonomy">
<paragraph id="5AC69FB80FA1214164249496B6B7C3EC" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Taxonomy.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2CFF8C12CADA9EC624E17CE0D8B924E" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName id="4317340FD5D0E3646C3A74361E7421CB" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="7A6B2D107FABE321C78B29EFDE2C941F" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unclear for a long time. 
<taxonomicName id="ECEDD5843BA701F02B222DEE6B2113CA" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="5D8F18D4D714038B7682D58E92A5F518" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described, according to the original description, from Radde, central Amur [Khabarovsk region] (Graeser 1890) on the basis of a single male from the collection of Taylor 
<normalizedToken id="57F372DF8253DA083B976E2460A34B70" originalValue="Tancré">Tancre</normalizedToken>
, in comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="73F2BDB33E22AD7F65C1674560F4D38B" baseAuthorityName="Bremer" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila maxima" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="0238A1C8FA842986B8FE606CF56B6F67" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bremer, 1861). The 
<normalizedToken id="4E9F8AFFED694F7C768358F6D0772096" originalValue="Püngeler">Puengeler</normalizedToken>
collection, now in MNHU, contains a female specimen with a type label (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D5A3C4211735B5B9539266DC27F837D2" captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">64</figureCitation>
). One can be convinced from the information given by the handwriting of 
<normalizedToken id="45ECCBCF50C727B77E215F77E0B210E2" originalValue="Püngeler">Puengeler</normalizedToken>
on the opposite side of the collecting label (made in May 1905) that this is a true type specimen from the 
<normalizedToken id="7E96B970FB5E575257A34030FFF219BE" originalValue="Tancré">Tancre</normalizedToken>
collection and it is a female, not a male. Thus, Graeser was mistaken about the sex of the type specimen. The study of the genitalia of the type specimen reveals that 
<taxonomicName id="B19AD671683AB9C6811D9756AD6059D9" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="822926CD0E867F1F60A8D161DDAA1C69" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with the species known as 
<taxonomicName id="6581784898C25340933ACA56E8B766ED" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila mirabilis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="76E8CB6B12BB3537BF4F69B42249A315" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bryk, 1948). 
<taxonomicName id="DB721496FC0654A1C6D77D7C477D40B2" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila mirabilis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="AED0F497DB8AD9A319241EB1AB864352" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore, is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="1C48C26BF91DF91689CF72205810AA59" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="ACB854D363E3FCCB7FA1116BE32692AC" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, syn. n.
</paragraph>
