<subSubSection id="CB59BBD987D1094C57D146E56E49406C" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D6C35BB240CA1CD881E40917F2B57C4E" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4589EFEC3E8AEEAED1D0E380FFC1F628" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
The distinctive features of 
<taxonomicName id="E4529B0EB1B5DE5B85FB1A1832A8A599" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="7789C896DF053E544A42AE9D393CCB6E" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8D1EF4D40BC71918A278E3106F54F6CE" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis id="DC8A9B829510CF9E5AFED545259E3F79" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BC3DA9FE53E8A5771F84B3B934832A4F" captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">66</figureCitation>
) are given in the works of 
<bibRefCitation id="0F3775FCCB1AEF6876AA5D8D65C2C075" author="Sviridov, AV" journalOrPublisher="Kiev" pageId="12" pageNumber="119" pagination="97 - 100" refId="B15" refString="Sviridov, AV, 1990. K tipovym materialam sovok, opisannyh F. Brikom iz Korei. In: Novosti faunistiki i sistematiki. Kiev: 97 - 100" title="K tipovym materialam sovok, opisannyh F. Brikom iz Korei." volumeTitle="Novosti faunistiki i sistematiki." year="1990">Sviridov (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="CA5949E6103761DC1B82484BCE70094B" author="Kononenko, VS" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Koreana" pageId="11" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 26" refId="B4" refString="Kononenko, VS, 1996. A revised catalogue of types of the Noctuidae (Lepidoptera) described by F. Bryk (1948) from the Korean Peninsula. Insecta Koreana 13: 1 - 26" title="A revised catalogue of types of the Noctuidae (Lepidoptera) described by F. Bryk (1948) from the Korean Peninsula." volume="13" year="1996">Kononenko (1996)</bibRefCitation>
(under the names 
<taxonomicName id="FF68394BB5D47AAFDB305FDF96493BE2" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis id="4564ABBE778AE5B1667C9B1E69C3EF7F" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3B4907B125D7690E795F1E8E1CBB5118" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila mirabilis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="32BBE3FB5E3D505F5BE9AEA3968D57F4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The main external differences between the two species are found in the colouration and shape of the forewing: 
<taxonomicName id="09822A8865F95F72328BD83BA36EF189" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="30E6F834D94283E48F97CE8E0A3EC196" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is broader winged and paler in colouration, usually ochreous brown to buff coloured, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4110B9425E89ACE422522A9E51283235" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis id="4C998F058A1A517FACCC2AF7F20032B2" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is darker, deep brown to claret brown, most often with a clearly visible violaceous shade and the forewing apex is somewhat more pointed. In the majority of the specimens the reniform stigma of 
<taxonomicName id="903CC574B65820B34E92975F32417D42" authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis id="7B3B48F528E2A9B555AF1E86F29F2457" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stronger, sharper, and more distinctly marked against the paler background. The female genitalia differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="F78A1FE2B4053F909F744FBFAC03BEB6" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis id="B19D563BC759F02FB31616D659AAF9C9" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3BADB990BCE04492555AF9E58794BD00" captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">69</figureCitation>
) by the shallower incision of the posterior margin of the antrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5AF6A89E8370DAA48821D41490E762B" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph id="68EFE9EED16614880AA212768475A3B9" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3FDE43E4E202BB7FF43923A7F64566F8" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Wingspan 44-49 mm. Head and body brownish grey; collar dark chocolate brown. Forewing brownish grey with sparse dark brown irroration; subbasal line indistinct; antemedial line arched with costal patch; reniform stigma large, dark brown, consists of 5 or 6 streak-like spots; orbicular stigma absent; postmedial and subterminal lines distinct; terminal line a row of black dots. Hindwing brownish; small discal spot present on underside; outer third dark brown; fringes as ground color.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D522B7F2BB7B405AE62A887B12D5A01D" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B481F7A520E1EDC022B6E7575EB72D91" bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="708B8F6F725682B97A338106C0B45C67" captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">67</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="7B1B20F770A851B7BAE298BB2A1686FB" captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">68</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor long, papillae anales large, hairy with long setae on apical edges. Apophyses anteriores relatively short, apophyses posteriores thin, longer than apophyses anteriores. Antrum long, narrow anteriorly, dilated posteriorly, ostium broad, posterior margin with small U-shaped cleft. Corpus bursae membranous, ovoid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
